benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/customFields - Retrieve bundle custom fields

covered: Valid Request scenarios returning 200 with a JSON array of CustomField objects (TC01, TC02, TC03, TC11, TC12, TC15, TC19, TC20) and audit levels NONE/FULL/MINIMAL
Empty Response handling when no custom fields (TC04)
Audit parameter handling: default NONE, FULL, MINIMAL and invalid/partial values (TC07, TC13, TC18) and extra param ignored (TC10)
Error handling: 404 bundle not found (TC05); 400 invalid bundleId (TC06); 400 invalid audit (TC07, TC13, TC18); 401 unauthorized (TC08); 503 service unavailability (TC09, TC16)
Security tests: SQL injection (TC17) and XSS (TC18)
Accessibility: Content-Type application/json and JSON array response (TC20)
gaps: Pagination handling for large datasets is not tested
Rate limiting / throttling scenarios are not tested
Caching behavior (ETag, Cache-Control, 304) is not tested
403 Forbidden scenario (insufficient permissions) not explicitly tested (only 401 tested)
Internal server error (HTTP 500) scenarios are not tested (only 503 covered)
Additional edge-case coverage (e.g., extremely large datasets or unusual boundary conditions) could be expanded
recommendations: Add pagination tests to verify page size, page number, and proper handling of large result sets
Add rate limiting tests to ensure correct handling of excessive requests (e.g., 429 if supported)
Add caching tests to validate ETag/Cache-Control headers and conditional requests (e.g., 304 Not Modified)
Add explicit 403 Forbidden scenarios to cover insufficient permissions
Add tests for 500 Internal Server Error scenarios to complement 503 Service Unavailable
Consider additional concurrency/stress tests across multiple bundles and concurrent audit service interactions
